{{nihongo|'''Kashihara Jingū'''|橿原神宮||}} is a [[Jinja (shrine)|Shinto shrine]] located in [[Kashihara, Nara|Kashihara]], [[Nara Prefecture|Nara]], [[Japan]].  
Kashihara Jingū was built in [[1889]] at the site of the Kashihara-gu where Japan's first emperor, [[Jinmu]], is said to have acceded to the throne. 


