The {{Nihongo|'''Kashihara Shrine'''|橿原神宮|Kashihara Jingū}} is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|en|Shinto shrine|qid=Q845945|lt=Shinto shrine|1=Shinto shrine}} located in the city of {{ill|Kashihara, Nara|en|Kashihara, Nara|qid=Q496319|lt=Kashihara|1=Kashihara, Nara}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|en|Nara Prefecture|qid=Q131287|lt=Nara Prefecture|1=Nara Prefecture}}, {{ill|Japan|en|Japan|qid=Q17|lt=Japan|1=Japan}}. The shrine was built in 2 April {{ill|1890|en|1890|qid=Q7832|lt=1890|1=1890}} at the site of the Kashihara-gū, which is situated on the southeastern side of {{ill|Mount Unebi|en|Mount Unebi|qid=Q17606448|lt=Mount Unebi|1=Mount Unebi}} of {{ill|Yamato Sanzan|en|Yamato Sanzan|qid=Q1470150|lt=Yamato Sanzan|1=Yamato Sanzan}}. Japan's first Emperor, {{ill|Emperor Jimmu|en|Emperor Jimmu|qid=Q200188|lt=Emperor Jimmu|1=Emperor Jimmu}}, is said to have acceded to the throne on {{ill|National Foundation Day (Japan)|en|National Foundation Day (Japan)|qid=Q1059995|lt=11 February|1=National Foundation Day (Japan)}} 660 BC at the Kashihara-gū.

The Mausoleum of Emperor Jimmu is found on the shrine's premises.

==Access==
*a 10-minute walk from the center gate of [[:en:Kashiharajingu-mae Station|Kashiharajingu-mae Station]] on {{ill|Kintetsu Railway|en|Kintetsu Railway|qid=Q1531085|lt=Kintetsu|1=Kintetsu Railway}} Lines ({{ill|Minami Osaka Line|en|Minami Osaka Line|qid=Q901342|lt=Minami Osaka Line|1=Minami Osaka Line}}, {{ill|Yoshino Line|en|Yoshino Line|qid=Q901085|lt=Yoshino Line|1=Yoshino Line}}, {{ill|Kashihara Line|en|Kashihara Line|qid=Q2491066|lt=Kashihara Line|1=Kashihara Line}}s).

